  "concept": "Shopping is full of \"I'll take it\" and \"I like them\" — so this unit teaches direct object pronouns (le, la, les): the little words that replace a noun you've already mentioned, so you don't repeat it.\n\nThey match the noun's gender and number:\n  le (masculine):  le pantalon → Je le prends. (I'll take it.)\n  la (feminine):   la robe → Je la prends.\n  l' (before a vowel): Je l'aime. (I like it.)\n  les (plural):    les chaussures → Je les achète. (I'll buy them.)\nThe key placement rule: the pronoun goes BEFORE the verb, unlike English. \"I like it\" → « Je l'aime » — literally \"I it-like.\"\n\nThe clothes: un vêtement (a garment), une robe (dress), un pantalon (trousers), une chemise (shirt), des chaussures (shoes), un manteau (coat). The verbs: porter (to wear), essayer (to try on), acheter (to buy). And the shopping talk: le prix (price), cher / chère (expensive).\n\nA shop exchange in action:\n  « Tu aimes cette robe ? — Oui, je l'aime, mais elle est trop chère. Je préfère la chemise — je la prends. »\n\nPick an item of clothing you like and say you'll take it, using le, la or les correctly.",
